If you were disturbed about the intruder who jumped the White House fence on March 10 and disturbed that somehow he was able to be on the grounds for 17 minutes before he got caught, you may want to hold onto yourself to keep from blowing a gasket when you read this. 
There were reasons that he was able to be on the grounds for that long, according to the Washington Examiner. 
